Mauritius Value Added Tax Receipts Increased 10.2% in 2010

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-03-11T10:47:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/mauritius-value-added-tax-receipts-increased-10-2-in-2010.html
Mauritius value added tax receipts
increased 10.2 percent to 21.1 billion rupees ($717 million)
last year, said Sudhamo Lal, director-general of the Mauritius
Revenue Authority.  Revenue exceeded the 20.75 billion-rupee target, Lal said
in an e-mailed response to questions. The forecast for next year
is 22.8 billion rupees, he said.  Total revenue from various direct and indirect taxes this
fiscal year is forecasted at 52.5 billion rupees, Lal said on
Jan. 19.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in  Port Louis  via Johannesburg at 
1933 or  gbell16@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin  at    asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 